      Important information

      Safety Information

      For external use only. Avoid contact with eyes. Keep away from naked flame or direct heat sources. Do not apply to sensitive skin. Do not apply to broken or inflamed skin. If irritation develops, reduce frequency or discontinue use.

      Ingredients

      mint lavender sandalwood cedar and rich amber.

      Directions

      Important: Keep in cool dry places.

      Question:

      United Kingdom. Burberry is a luxury British design house founded by Thomas Burberry in 1856. This house distinguished itself with fashion and accessories, including a now-iconic trench coat and the brand's unique and recognizable tartan pattern which has become one of the most-copied motifs in fashion. Burberry was gr see more United Kingdom. Burberry is a luxury British design house founded by Thomas Burberry in 1856. This house distinguished itself with fashion and accessories, including a now-iconic trench coat and the brand's unique and recognizable tartan pattern which has become one of the most-copied motifs in fashion. Burberry was granted a Royal Warrant for Clothing from the British Royal Family. In addition to their fashion line and accessories, the Burberry brand offers an exclusive line of fragrances for men and women-many in bottles adorned with the company's signature tartan-under arrangement with Inter Parfums. Their first perfume, Burberry for Men, appeared in 1981.
      Designer Burberry has 50 perfumes in our fragrance base. The earliest edition was created in 1981 and the newest is from 2013. Burberry fragrances were made in collaboration with perfumers Michel Girard, Nathalie Gracia-Cetto, Antoine Maisondieu, Antoine Lie, Dominique Ropion, Anne Flipo, Olivier Polge, Emilie (Bevierre) Coppermann, Creations Aromatiques, Sonia Constant, Beatrice Piquet, Mark Buxton, Michel Almairac, Jean-Marc Chaillan, Domitille Bertier, Jean-Pierre Bethouart and Nathalie Lorson. see less       United Kingdom.       Dave Gingerich
      4.0 out of 5 stars A pleasant surprise
      Reviewed in the United States on July 5, 2008
      Verified Purchase
      I had never used or sampled this scent before but took a chance due to the nice reviews and the nice price from Amazon.
      The first time I used it I was a bit taken aback ... but by the end of the day I had come to really enjoy its subtle, spicy scent. This is a somewhat strong or heavy EDT when first applied, that's not a criticism as it does mean you can use less and your 3.3 oz will last longer, but because I didn't know what to expect, I was a bit overwhelmed.
      However, once the EDT had had a chance to blend for 30 minutes or so, I found it quite attractive. And the best part, is it is one of the longest lasting EDTs I have used recently (including several from Polo, Ck, Kenneth Cole, ...).
      I would characterize this as more of a fall or winter scent due to the earthy, spicey, slightly musk smell. It is probably least suited for daytime summer use. But during fall or winter, you could use this day or night. I could see myself continuing to use it during wintery spring evenings (in Colorado, they last until mid-April) but it would not be high on my list for any use during the summer.
      All in all, I was pleasantly surprised. This is a very good scent, it lasts a long time and is available here for a good price.
      Now I'm interested in trying some of the other Burberry scents ...
